value.0: Good Eve, Welcome to the Hafin.. Be sure to enjoy your stay here.

Yes I am the Owner of this lovely place. Every place deserves a bit of charm and class even a darkened place like this.. The name came from my father's side. He was German.... the word Hafin means Haven...
Oh anything... and everything... The Troubles that exist outside these walls should be forgotten.
Ahh the other clans... which would you care to know about.
Every masterwork must have its frame; every bust must have its pillar. This the Ventrue understand, and they perform their functions admirably.
To experience this clan's alien fruits would be almost worth the price. Remember well that "almost," dear one.

One deals with the butcher and the bureaucrat because they provide useful conveniences. One graciously acknowledges services efficiently performed. One does not, though, invite the hired help to the soiree, nor take kindly to party-crashers.
The subjects of many delightful stories - well, delightful so long as one does not also feature in the tale.
Odious beasts! And to think that they are allowed in the halls of culture! Oh, how gauche...
The fractured kaleidoscope of their thoughts is enchanting at first glimpse. Gaze at it too long, though, and one grows prone to terrible headaches.
Their Miltonian conceit is dreadfully provocative, or provocatively dreadful, but they take it all so seriously.
As charmingly untamed as a tiger; as worthy of consideration as a housecat.

It is inevitable, of course, that persons of Epicurean refinement will in the course of eternity engage in dealings with those of...unsavory character. Record well any transactions made, and repay all favors promptly.
On the first night, their passion terrifies. On the second night, their passion fascinates. On the third night, their passion inflames. After that...frankly, their passion begins to bore.
There is beauty in what they do, make no mistake, but it is a beauty best observed from a distance

We Toreador put a fair degree of stock in lineage; a vampire fortunate enough to descend from a favored sire is lavished with adoration (to her face, anyway) , while childer of a sire "on the outs" suffer social humiliation. Few of these lines deviate from the main clan in any significant way.

Toreador have little practical organization, though our cliquishness and social networks are legendary . The clan meets frequently, but more as an excuse to host lavish parties and showings than to accomplish anything. Status among the Toreador is a tempestuous whirlwind in which one subtle smile or catty critique can lead to fortune or disaster; a prodigy may be adored one night, commit a barely perceptible faux pas, and be ostracized the next. Do try and remember that childe.

Toreador are preternaturally attuned to the aesthetic and beautiful, but this sensitivity can prove dangerous. When a Toreador views, hears or even smells something that is truly beautiful - a person, a painting, a song, a particularly lovely sunrise - we often become entranced by the sensation. and will stand in rapt fascination for a scene or until the beautiful thing withdraws. Enraptured Toreador may not even defend themselves if attacked, though being wounded may snap us out of it.

Toreador range across a spectrum of concepts, from lonely, tortured artists to debauched playwrites. Some Toreador are Embraced for no reason other than their beauty or personal style, as a passionate sire decides that they simply must be preserved for eternity.

Auspex is a Discipline that grants vampires supernatural senses. It is one of the most common and favored Discipline among Cainites due to its versatility and overall usefulness in just about every facet of vampiric existence. Celerity is a Discipline that grants vampires supernatural speed and finesse by expending vitae. Presence, the discipline of unnatural attraction and emotional control. This discipline is the ultimate exaltation of the "Power of personality" that many kindred have.

We take care to ensure that our havens are comfortable, convenient for socializing and - above all conform to our own aesthetic tastes. Vampires of a more artistic bent might maintain spacious lofts to display their works, while their "poseur" counterparts love opulent suites perfect for hosting parties.
Are you the owner? How did you come up with the name?
Haven... Haven from what?
That if very nice of you to try and help others like that.
